king. The mmap'ed patches may be around and<br />flushed, but the logic to not allow currently *active* mmaps (with the<br />rather nasty random -EBUSY return value) should mean that there is no<br />race.<br /><br />Or rather, there's a race, but it results in that EBUSY thing.<br /><br />With my simplfied locking, the sync_blockdev() is right before (not a<br />few lines prior) to the kill_bdev(), and in a perfect world they'd<br />actually be one single operation ("write back and invalidate pages<br />with the wrong block-size"). But they aren't.<br /><br />                Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
